<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7452&amp;p=32053#p32053"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Ivo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Classic Shell does not overwrite XML or DirectUI data.<br /></div><br /><br />Ok, I thought it does when modifying default properties such as colorization of the taskbar, opacity / transparency and spacing between icons.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Doing anything like this is a guaranteed way to get an endless list of compatibility bugs. Unlike Microsoft I don't have a compatibility lab with access to thousands of applications to play with.<br /></div><br /><br />How does Bbleanskin titlebar work then and why does it function in &quot;Open&quot; and &quot;Save as&quot; boxes? <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://bb4win.sourceforge.net/index.html">http://bb4win.sourceforge.net/index.html</a><!-- m -->. It just blanks explorer dwm titlebar and puts a proprietary bar of a given height on top of it which is additionally packed with a set of caption buttons and &quot;Label&quot; box. On my end, it works flawlessly and has no compatibility issues. Is that bar any different from all the other bars with added functionality that are being developed for windows?<br /><br />By the way is it theoretically possible to resize icons in Details View?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=18727">Sobrium Clot</a> — Thu Mar 30, 2017 12:48 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
