<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Sobrium Clot]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-03-30T05:36:19-07:00</updated>
<published>2017-03-30T05:36:19-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7452&amp;p=32048#p32048</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7452&amp;p=32048#p32048"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Why Classic Toolbar does not work in &quot;save as&quot; dialog box]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7452&amp;p=32048#p32048"><![CDATA[
Its kinda question that has been bothering me for quite a while since the first time I installed QTTabBar &amp; Classic shell goodies on my machine. Neither QTTabBar's toolbars nor Classic Bar are visible in &quot;Save as&quot; and &quot;Open&quot; Common Dialog Boxes. These are the boxes that appear when u open a new file through the application menu (photoshop, paint whatever) or when u save a file as a new one.<br /><br />Could anyone just tell me why Classic Toolbar does not work in Common Boxes? Basically QTTabBar, DmexBar, CS provide toolbars with extra functionality that are capable of replacing native windows shell elements such as address bar or navigation pane. But this makes a little to no sense since disabling native explorer's nav bar and/or nav pane means that u WILL NOT be able to browse while in Common Dialog Boxes. With nav bar disabled I couldnt even save an image from my web browser to the directory I want. Thats the reason why I dont use Classic shell. Nor will I ever install other third-party add-ons unless they are proven workable in Common Dialog Boxes.<br /><br />Having said that I want to know whats difficult in making toolbars WORK in both normal explorer window and Common Dialog Boxes such as &quot;Save as&quot; box and &quot;Open&quot; box. Is it really that complex to implement?<br /><br />Question #2. I know Classic Shell allows to increase spacing between icons in Tree View. See attachments.<br /><br />Since CS does overwrite windows default XML and DirectUI preferences stored in explorerframe.dll and shell32.dll I think that it might be possible to take advantage of this and manipulate spacing between icons in Details View.<br /><br />Or totally change the size of icons from 16 to 24 or 20. Which is what I wanna do.<br /><br />Is that possible? Can Details View icons be resized? Is there a way to increase spacing between icons in Small Icons View, Details View?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=18727">Sobrium Clot</a> — Thu Mar 30, 2017 5:36 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
